Go feed the ducks, will you?

512
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,833
Oh, Tallulah.

513
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,194
I said, beat it.

514
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,112
Long time no see.

515
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:33,433
- You know how it is.
- Yeah.

516
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:37,711
You used to come see me every night.

517
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:40,394
- I've been busy.
- Busy doing what?

518
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:42,149
This and that.

519
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:48,515
Fizzy, cut the ivory
and hit the shoe leather.

520
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:51,276
Yes, ma'am.

521
00:37:58,120 --> 00:37:59,269
You're aces, Bugsy.

522
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:02,719
I always found you special.

523
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:05,310
Careful, you're racing my mother.

524
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:08,119
Come on, give a girl a break.

525
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,918
Sure you've got the right fella?

526
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:12,594
- You're not like those other saps.
- No?

527
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:13,711
No.

528
00:38:15,160 --> 00:38:17,116
You've got lovely brown eyes.

529
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,789
They'll be black eyes
if Fat Sam catches us.

530
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:24,034
- How about smearing my lipstick?
- Careful.

531
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:27,352
If you come any closer,
I'll have to call my lawyer.

532
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:29,551
So call him.

533
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:39,716
Blousey.

534
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,117
Blousey.

535
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:44,509
Blousey.

536
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,796
It's the broad about the audition.

537
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:54,918
He's busy. Come back tomorrow.

538
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,436
No, no, no.

539
00:38:57,240 --> 00:38:59,959
Hey, honey. I'm all ears.
Be with you in a minute.

540
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:04,559
Carry on as normal.
Don't let 'em know we're beat.

541
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,438
- Business as usual.
- Right.

542
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:08,192
- Calm and collected.
- Right.

543
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:10,590
So they don't know we're
scared. I mean, concerned.

544
00:39:11,160 --> 00:39:11,751
Sure, boss.

545
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:28,073
<i>I'm feeling fine...</i>

546
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:31,394
<i>filled with emotions...</i>

547
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:34,753
<i>stronger than wine...</i>

548
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:37,435
<i>they give me the notion...</i>

549
00:39:37,680 --> 00:39:40,558
<i>that this strange new feeling...</i>

550
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:45,436
<i>is something that</i>
<i>you're feeling too.</i>

551
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,718
<i>Matter of fact...</i>

552
00:39:54,040 --> 00:39:56,793
<i>I'm forced to admit it...</i>

553
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:59,271
<i>caught in the act...</i>

554
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:02,357
<i>and maybe we've hit it...</i>

555
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:05,957
<i>this strange new feeling...</i>

556
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:09,232
<i>is something you're feeling...</i>

557
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:11,470
Okay, honey. That's enough.

558
00:40:12,600 --> 00:40:16,115
A little contemporary for
me, but very nice. You're hired.

559
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:29,953
That was great. That
really was. Terrific.

560
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:34,236
Blousey.

561
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:36,399
Come back, will you?

562
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,992
What's the use?

563
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:40,550
I've got to go.

564
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:48,910
Blousey.

565
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:52,669
Where is she? Blousey.

566
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:22,072
Show's going swell.

567
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:24,038
Just the way I want it to be.

568
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,151
Same number of
drinks, same everything.

569
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,991
They mustn't know
they've got us on the run.

570
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,879
Here, I wanna show you something.

571
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:40,678
I've sent for someone to
help us out of our predicament.

572
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:43,236
No ten-cent dummy. A specialist.

573
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:44,636
A doctor?

574
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,628
Not a doctor, a hoodlum.

575
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:50,637
I thought we were hoodlums.

576
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:53,759
Not a dumb bum. This
guy is the real McCoy.

577
00:41:54,240 --> 00:41:55,639
Not Looney Bergonzi!

578
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:56,869
<i>The</i> Looney Bergonzi?

579
00:41:57,080 --> 00:42:00,675
The very same, mad
as a hatter, Bergonzi.

580
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:03,834
Best man in Chicago.
Here's what we do.

581
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,836
We meet Dandy Dan.
Looney hides in the back seat.

582
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:09,559
- You drive.
- Right.

583
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:14,231
- But I don't drive.
- You what?

584
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:16,796
You don't drive?

585
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:20,154
Then we get ourselves a driver.

586
00:42:28,080 --> 00:42:30,071
- Hi, Bugsy.
- Is Blousey there?

587
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:32,196
- She won't see you.
- Tell her I'm sick.

588
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:34,391
- You're sick?
- Sick of waiting.

589
00:42:38,640 --> 00:42:39,470
Beat it.

590
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:41,552
Give a guy a break.

591
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:43,315
I brought you some flowers.

592
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:44,954
I'll see Tallulah gets them.

593
00:42:45,160 --> 00:42:47,310
Quit being smart. They're for you.

594
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:48,549
Five minutes, girls.

595
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,756
- I have to go.
- I was thinking of getting a job.

596
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:53,151
You don't get paid for
standing in bread lines.

597
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:57,632
A legit job. We could save
enough money to go to Hollywood.

598
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,558
Believe it when I see it.

599
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:04,715
- Bugsy, you drive?
- Sure, why?

600
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:08,316
- Like to earn some green stuff?
- Long as it ain't cabbages.

601
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:11,075
Step inside. I got
a proposition for you.

602
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:13,869
Flowers? For me?

603
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:15,997
How nice.

604
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:18,157
Put these in water.

605
00:43:28,520 --> 00:43:29,316
Hello?

606
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:35,230
Who shall I say is
calling? One moment.

607
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,635
- Hello.
- Dandy Dan, is that you?

608
00:44:07,360 --> 00:44:09,920
- This is Dandy Dan speaking.
- I wanna arrange a meeting.

609
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:13,511
- Sure. Where?
- Outta town.

610
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:16,359
Agreed. Just you and a driver.

611
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:19,996
- When?
- Monday. 11 A.M..

612
00:44:20,360 --> 00:44:21,349
Right, I'll be there.

613
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:23,718
<i>Got him, the knuckle.</i>

614
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:25,673
<i>Got him, the salami.</i>

615
00:44:25,840 --> 00:44:27,796
Let's go and enjoy the show.

616
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:39,750
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

617
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:41,792
<i>my first rule of thumb...</i>

618
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:46,632
<i>I don't say where I'm going,</i>
<i>or where I'm coming from.</i>

619
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:51,278
<i>I try to leave a little</i>
<i>reputation behind me...</i>

620
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:56,079
<i>so if you really need to,</i>
<i>you'll know how to find me.</i>

621
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,310
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

622
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:09,352
<i>I live till I die...</i>

623
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:11,154
<i>I'll take what you give me...</i>

624
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:14,118
<i>and I won't ask why.</i>

625
00:45:14,520 --> 00:45:17,910
<i>I've made a lot of friends</i>
<i>in exotic places...</i>

626
00:45:19,120 --> 00:45:20,189
<i>I don't remember names...</i>

627
00:45:20,360 --> 00:45:23,670
<i>but I remember faces.</i>

628
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:39,917
<i>Lonely, you don't</i>
<i>have to be lonely...</i>

629
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:48,150
<i>come see Tallulah, we can</i>
<i>chase your troubles away.</i>

630
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:53,790
<i>If you're lonely...</i>

631
00:45:53,960 --> 00:45:58,238
<i>you don't have to be lonely.</i>

632
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:04,111
<i>When they talk to Tallulah,</i>
<i>you know what they say...</i>

633
00:46:04,880 --> 00:46:08,953
<i>no one south of heaven's</i>
<i>gonna treat you finer...</i>

634
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:13,671
<i>Tallulah had her training</i>
<i>in North Carolina.</i>

635
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:24,955
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

636
00:46:25,120 --> 00:46:26,792
<i>and soon I'll be gone...</i>

637
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:31,479
<i>an open invitation</i>
<i>is the road I travel on.</i>

638
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:36,312
<i>I never say goodbye</i>
<i>because the words upset me.</i>

639
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:38,756
<i>You may forgive my going...</i>

640
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:41,434
<i>but you won't forget me.</i>

641
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:52,920
<i>Lonely...</i>

642
00:46:53,080 --> 00:46:57,437
<i>you don't have to be lonely...</i>

643
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:05,237
<i>come see Tallulah, we can</i>
<i>chase your troubles away.</i>

644
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:11,037
<i>If you're lonely...</i>

645
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:15,796
<i>you don't have to be lonely...</i>

646
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:21,358
<i>when they talk about Tallulah,</i>
<i>you know what they say...</i>

647
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:26,238
<i>no one south of heaven's</i>
<i>gonna treat you finer...</i>

648
00:47:26,520 --> 00:47:31,196
<i>Tallulah had her training</i>
<i>in North Carolina.</i>

649
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:14,431
They're coming.

650
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:15,915
Looney, keep your head down.

651
00:48:37,880 --> 00:48:39,029
What can I do for you?

652
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:41,476
How about some straight talk?

653
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:42,630
Suits me.

654
00:48:42,800 --> 00:48:45,439
- You've been taking liberties.
- I've been taking what's mine.

655
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:47,875
- Trouble is, it belongs to me.
- Too bad.

656
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:51,637
I'm sure we can talk
it over. I'm a businessman.

657
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:53,837
Yeah, a dime-a-dozen gangster.

658
00:48:54,080 --> 00:48:56,196
Button your lip.
Don't talk dirty to me.

659
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:58,794
I don't like your
mouth. Have some respect.

660
00:48:59,160 --> 00:49:01,469
You'd slit your own
throat for two bits.

661
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:03,471
Keep your wisecracks.

662
00:49:04,600 --> 00:49:05,589
Keep talking.

663
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:07,831
I have my position to think of.

664
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,116
Right now it's not worth a nickel.

665
00:49:10,280 --> 00:49:12,157
You're a dirty rat, Dan.

666
00:49:12,320 --> 00:49:14,436
You've been watching
too many movies.

667
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:16,429
Okay, Looney, let him have it.

668
00:49:16,680 --> 00:49:18,318
Charlie, Yonkers,
it's a double-cross.

669
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:20,832
Okay, freeze.

670
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:29,751
Looney.

671
00:49:32,520 --> 00:49:34,078
What's the matter with you?

672
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:44,875
Hey, you guys.

673
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:45,870
Over here!

674
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:47,069
Over here!

675
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,638
Come back, dummies!
They're getting away.

676
00:49:52,080 --> 00:49:53,195
Come back here.

677
00:49:53,760 --> 00:49:57,469
Come on, step on it.

678
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:00,949
Come on, let's go.

679
00:50:12,040 --> 00:50:13,234
We're going to lose them.

680
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:14,829
Drive faster.

681
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:28,829
Dan, you're a rat!

682
00:50:32,360 --> 00:50:33,679
You're a dirty rat!

683
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:35,513
Come on, they're gonna get us.

684
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:45,708
Hold tight, Mr. Stacetto.

685
00:51:10,040 --> 00:51:10,677
Come on, Malone.

686
00:51:12,160 --> 00:51:14,879
You're a dirty
double-crossing rat!

687
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:17,991
Look out.

688
00:51:21,080 --> 00:51:21,671
Don't stop!

689
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:22,556
There's a bridge!

690
00:51:22,760 --> 00:51:23,795
Put the brakes on!

691
00:51:26,960 --> 00:51:29,110
We lost them.

692
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:39,956
Go and cluck somewhere else.

693
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:44,079
Here. Get yourself a new suit.

694
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:46,479
Get rid of the sack you're wearing.

695
00:51:46,920 --> 00:51:49,388
Thank you, Mr. Stacetto.

696
00:51:49,560 --> 00:51:51,391
Here's my tailor's card.

697
00:51:51,800 --> 00:51:53,756
You ain't got to
pay for six months.

698
00:51:54,360 --> 00:51:55,270
Thank you very much.

699
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:58,716
Think nothing
of it. Let's go.

700
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:09,191
What do you think?
Don't I look cute?

701
00:52:10,200 --> 00:52:10,837
I don't know.

702
00:52:11,120 --> 00:52:12,348
Come on, Dotty,
what do you think?

703
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,957
I think the color's wrong.

704
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:16,673
What are you talking about?

705
00:52:16,840 --> 00:52:18,592
Purple's my color.

706
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:20,269
Don't I always wear purple?

707
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:21,668
It matches your nose.

708
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:22,875
Maybe it's the length.

709
00:52:23,280 --> 00:52:26,397
It's the latest length. Look!

710
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:30,075
Maybe the frills stick out
too much. Like your ears.

711
00:52:30,840 --> 00:52:33,115
Frills are in. Look at
this photo of Lena Marelli.

712
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:35,231
Lena Marelli is
not Bangles Dobell.

713
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:37,595
You think it'd
look better on you?

714
00:52:37,760 --> 00:52:38,875
It'd look better on a horse.

715
00:52:39,280 --> 00:52:42,636
Jealous. Can I help it if my
looks are ahead of their time?

716
00:52:43,240 --> 00:52:44,116
What?

717
00:52:44,440 --> 00:52:45,190
Full of character.

718
00:52:45,400 --> 00:52:45,991
Kind of earthy.

719
00:52:46,160 --> 00:52:47,559
Like a bucket of mud.

720
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:50,276
You creep. Get lost!

721
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:57,309
How about you? Do you
think I look terrible?

722
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:02,673
Do I look cute or terrible?

723
00:53:06,240 --> 00:53:06,831
Honestly?

724
00:53:07,640 --> 00:53:10,996
Bangles Dobell, you look terrible.

725
00:53:13,360 --> 00:53:14,270
What are you looking at?

726
00:53:15,240 --> 00:53:15,877
Nothing.

727
00:53:52,720 --> 00:53:53,357
<i>Blousey.</i>

728
00:54:00,600 --> 00:54:01,271
Blousey.

729
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:09,671
Blousey.

730
00:54:10,680 --> 00:54:11,954
It's for you. It's Bugsy.

731
00:54:15,720 --> 00:54:16,675
Give him my love.

732
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:19,191
Thanks.

733
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:20,551
Hello.

734
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:22,592
Blousey, it's Bugsy.

735
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:23,351
Where are you?

736
00:54:23,520 --> 00:54:27,433
Around. I can't talk,
but I just made 200 bucks.

737
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:29,039
You printed it yourself?

738
00:54:29,360 --> 00:54:30,509
No, I earned it.

739
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:31,397
Doing what?

740
00:54:31,720 --> 00:54:32,516
Oh, this and that.

741
00:54:32,960 --> 00:54:34,188
Hang on a minute.

742
00:54:34,680 --> 00:54:35,669
I can't hear you.

743
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,398
There's a train going by.

744
00:54:38,720 --> 00:54:39,630
Who gave you the money?

745
00:54:40,800 --> 00:54:41,391
Fat Sam.

746
00:54:41,680 --> 00:54:43,318
He gave you 200 dollars?

747
00:54:43,680 --> 00:54:45,557
And the loan of his
sedan for the afternoon.

748
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:47,313
He loaned you his sedan?

749
00:54:47,800 --> 00:54:49,472
I don't believe it.
You're putting me on.

750
00:54:52,400 --> 00:54:53,196
I believe you.

751
00:54:55,840 --> 00:54:57,114
<i>He's a sinner...</i>

752
00:54:58,240 --> 00:54:59,992
<i>candy-coated...</i>

753
00:55:00,920 --> 00:55:04,993
<i>he always seems to be alone...</i>

754
00:55:06,520 --> 00:55:12,072
<i>but they love him,</i>
<i>Bugsy Malone.</i>

755
00:55:16,080 --> 00:55:17,559
<i>A city slicker...</i>

756
00:55:18,800 --> 00:55:21,553
<i>he can charm you with a smile...</i>

757
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:24,594
<i>a style all his own...</i>

758
00:55:26,040 --> 00:55:29,191
<i>everybody loves that man...</i>

759
00:55:29,760 --> 00:55:32,718
<i>Bugsy Malone.</i>

760
00:55:39,200 --> 00:55:40,997
<i>Hard-headed Bugsy...</i>

761
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:42,593
<i>makes his mind up...</i>

762
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:47,592
<i>don't mess with Bugsy,</i>
<i>or you'll wind up...</i>

763
00:55:48,760 --> 00:55:52,673
<i>wishing you'd left him alone.</i>

764
00:55:53,840 --> 00:55:56,673
<i>He's a man, a mountain,</i>
<i>he's a rolling stone...</i>

765
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:00,758
<i>and when he leaves you...</i>

766
00:56:01,640 --> 00:56:03,198
<i>sad and lonely...</i>

767
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:05,555
<i>cry, I couldn't say.</i>

768
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:07,673
<i>But it's known...</i>

769
00:56:08,800 --> 00:56:12,270
<i>that everybody</i>
<i>wants that man...</i>

770
00:56:12,680 --> 00:56:15,148
<i>Bugsy Malone.</i>

771
00:56:26,280 --> 00:56:27,872
Mustard with onions or ketchup?

772
00:56:28,040 --> 00:56:28,790
Mustard with onions.

773
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:30,628
Oh, and this, too.

774
00:56:31,040 --> 00:56:33,190
- What's this?
- A present.

775
00:56:33,360 --> 00:56:34,588
- Open it up.
- You got to be kidding.

776
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:35,949
I don't kid around.

777
00:56:36,480 --> 00:56:38,675
It's beautiful.

778
00:56:39,240 --> 00:56:39,831
Nice, huh?

779
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:40,830
What is it?

780
00:56:41,200 --> 00:56:42,952
What is it? A viewer.

781
00:56:43,360 --> 00:56:44,873
Look through here.

782
00:56:45,320 --> 00:56:46,958
Pictures of Hollywood stars.

783
00:56:47,120 --> 00:56:47,950
Bugsy...

784
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:50,430
it's fantastic. It really is.

785
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:52,918
If only I could get to Hollywood.

786
00:56:53,160 --> 00:56:53,797
You can.

787
00:56:54,240 --> 00:56:54,877
Sure.

788
00:56:55,040 --> 00:56:56,109
I know, in the front row...

789
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:57,190
of the Roxy Theatre...

790
00:56:57,360 --> 00:56:58,190
on East 38th Street.

791
00:56:58,360 --> 00:57:00,112
No, really get to Hollywood.

792
00:57:00,560 --> 00:57:01,390
Keep talking.

793
00:57:01,560 --> 00:57:02,788
1.80 for the viewer, right?

794
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:04,839
10 cents for the hot dogs.

795
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:08,274
Leaves 198 dollars for...

796
00:57:08,480 --> 00:57:09,071
Surprise me.

797
00:57:09,240 --> 00:57:10,673
- Two tickets.
- Two tickets?

798
00:57:11,080 --> 00:57:12,115
How many tickets you need?

799
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:13,515
Two tickets to the ball game?

800
00:57:13,720 --> 00:57:15,039
To Hollywood, dummy.

801
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:18,148
This can't be true.
Are we really going?

802
00:57:18,320 --> 00:57:19,309
Knock it off.

803
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:20,590
You're putting me on.

804
00:57:21,040 --> 00:57:21,870
It's the honest truth.

805
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:23,509
I'm picking them up tomorrow.

806
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:26,314
Now I better get
Fat Sam's car back.

807
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:27,828
Or I'm not going anywhere.

808
00:58:06,960 --> 00:58:07,836
Is anyone in there?

809
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:11,711
Hello?

810
00:58:13,320 --> 00:58:13,911
Are you hurt?

811
00:58:17,400 --> 00:58:18,674
Help! Somebody
help me, please!

812
00:58:20,840 --> 00:58:21,795
Somebody, please!

813
00:58:21,960 --> 00:58:22,790
Somebody help!

814
00:58:24,160 --> 00:58:25,195
Help me, please!

815
00:58:38,920 --> 00:58:40,148
They take your money?

816
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:45,752
Yeah. Nearly 200 dollars.

817
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,669
Thanks anyway for helping me.

818
00:58:49,080 --> 00:58:49,751
It was nothing.

819
00:58:50,600 --> 00:58:52,397
- You must be a boxer, right?
- No.

820
00:58:52,960 --> 00:58:54,518
- You're not?
- No.

821
00:58:54,840 --> 00:58:56,319
Best punching I ever saw.

822
00:58:56,760 --> 00:58:58,318
- Ever been coached?
- No.

823
00:58:58,920 --> 00:59:00,717
- Ever thought of taking it up?
- No.

824
00:59:01,400 --> 00:59:03,356
Why not? You could be a champion.

825
00:59:03,960 --> 00:59:06,599
- Never had the chance.
- I know who could help you.

826
00:59:06,760 --> 00:59:08,716
- You know Cagey Joe?
- No.

827
00:59:09,240 --> 00:59:11,515
- You must know Slugger's Gym?
- No.

828
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:14,760
- You don't know much, do you?
- Nope.

829
00:59:15,480 --> 00:59:16,469
What's your name?

830
00:59:16,680 --> 00:59:18,432
Smith, Leroy Smith.

831
00:59:18,880 --> 00:59:20,916
I'm Bugsy Malone. Put it there.

832
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:22,754
You got yourself a manager.

833
00:59:24,080 --> 00:59:26,355
- Know the first thing I'm gonna do?
- No.

834
00:59:26,520 --> 00:59:29,034
Treat you to one heck of a meal.

835
00:59:29,240 --> 00:59:32,038
- Thought they took all your dough.
- Who needs money?

836
01:00:32,600 --> 01:00:34,716
Look at this, O'Dreary.

837
01:00:37,360 --> 01:00:39,430
You cracked it this time, Captain.

838
01:00:39,880 --> 01:00:41,518
Get the plaster.
We'll take a mold.

839
01:00:41,840 --> 01:00:43,068
Come on, get the plaster.

840
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:47,749
Careful. Up a bit.

841
01:00:48,120 --> 01:00:52,193
Left a bit.

842
01:00:52,520 --> 01:00:53,236
Come on, hurry up.

843
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:56,034
Hold it straight. Be careful.

844
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:04,194
You idiots!

845
01:01:07,760 --> 01:01:08,749
Hello. What?

846
01:01:09,040 --> 01:01:12,396
They got the still.
The whole lot's gone.

847
01:01:12,760 --> 01:01:16,116
Not the sarsaparilla racket,
too. Get round here now.

848
01:01:16,440 --> 01:01:17,873
- I can't, boss.
- Why not?

849
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:19,276
I'm all tied up.

850
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:21,830
I don't care if you're
busy. Get here right away.

851
01:01:22,960 --> 01:01:26,953
Careful, you idiots.

852
01:01:27,400 --> 01:01:28,230
O'Dreary.

853
01:01:28,600 --> 01:01:29,191
Don't worry...

854
01:01:29,360 --> 01:01:31,954
we'll break you out
at headquarters.

855
01:01:43,720 --> 01:01:46,678
- Hi, Bugsy. How you been?
- Swell, Cagey Joe.

856
01:01:47,160 --> 01:01:49,879
I'd like you to meet the
next heavyweight champion.

857
01:01:50,040 --> 01:01:51,553
Leroy, meet Cagey Joe.

858
01:01:51,800 --> 01:01:54,075
Cagey Joe, this is Leroy Smith.

859
01:01:54,480 --> 01:01:56,994
- Ever been in the ring before?
- No.

860
01:01:57,680 --> 01:01:59,636
- So you wanna be a fighter?
- No.

861
01:01:59,800 --> 01:02:01,995
Sure he does. He's a natural.

862
01:02:02,440 --> 01:02:03,350
Look at those fists.

863
01:02:03,640 --> 01:02:04,755
Did you ever see such fists?

864
01:02:05,320 --> 01:02:05,911
Hit it, Leroy.

865
01:02:08,760 --> 01:02:10,398
You see? A born champion.

866
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:11,910
What's your name again?

867
01:02:12,240 --> 01:02:13,958
Smith. Leroy Smith.

868
01:02:14,240 --> 01:02:16,629
With your help...

869
01:02:16,920 --> 01:02:18,319
he could be champion in no time.

870
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:30,031
<i>So you wanna be a boxer...</i>

871
01:02:30,440 --> 01:02:31,759
<i>in the golden ring.</i>

872
01:02:32,680 --> 01:02:34,636
<i>Can you punch like a train?</i>

873
01:02:34,920 --> 01:02:36,035
<i>Tell me just one thing...</i>

874
01:02:36,640 --> 01:02:39,598
<i>can you move like a</i>
<i>hummingbird's wing?</i>

875
01:02:39,960 --> 01:02:40,915
<i>Oh, that's fast!</i>

876
01:02:41,080 --> 01:02:43,992
<i>Can you bob, can you weave?</i>

877
01:02:44,840 --> 01:02:46,637
<i>Well, you might as well quit...</i>

878
01:02:47,080 --> 01:02:48,274
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

879
01:02:50,480 --> 01:02:53,677
<i>So you wanna be a boxer,</i>
<i>can you pass the test?</i>

880
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:58,037
<i>I can tell if you got it,</i>
<i>I've trained the best.</i>

881
01:02:59,280 --> 01:03:02,909
<i>When you work and sweat</i>
<i>like a buzz saw...</i>

882
01:03:03,080 --> 01:03:04,308
<i>and you near lose your mind...</i>

883
01:03:04,480 --> 01:03:06,232
<i>when you find out your</i>
<i>boy has a glass jaw.</i>

884
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:08,234
<i>So you might as well quit...</i>

885
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:10,388
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

886
01:03:12,280 --> 01:03:14,157
<i>Put him in the ring,</i>
<i>look at what you've found...</i>

887
01:03:14,400 --> 01:03:15,389
<i>we can use the fun...</i>

888
01:03:15,560 --> 01:03:16,276
<i>pushing him around.</i>

889
01:03:16,440 --> 01:03:17,919
<i>We'll show him the ropes...</i>

890
01:03:18,600 --> 01:03:20,238
<i>and destroy his hopes...</i>

891
01:03:21,120 --> 01:03:22,030
<i>put him in the ring...</i>

892
01:03:22,200 --> 01:03:24,316
<i>let him feel the sting...</i>

893
01:03:24,480 --> 01:03:25,151
<i>we can make him dance...</i>

894
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:26,753
<i>we'll pound him to bits...</i>

895
01:03:27,400 --> 01:03:30,710
<i>then he'll call it quits.</i>

896
01:03:34,080 --> 01:03:35,877
Come on, Leroy.

897
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:42,590
<i>So you wanna be a boxer,</i>
<i>wanna be the champ...</i>

898
01:03:43,720 --> 01:03:47,269
<i>there's a golden boy inside</i>
<i>you, not a punchy tramp...</i>

899
01:03:47,640 --> 01:03:50,518
<i>if you listen and you learn,</i>
<i>there's an honor you can earn...</i>

900
01:03:52,000 --> 01:03:54,992
<i>when you see the crown,</i>
<i>you're a king, not a clown.</i>

901
01:03:55,880 --> 01:03:57,108
<i>But you might as well quit...</i>

902
01:03:58,040 --> 01:03:59,268
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

903
01:04:01,120 --> 01:04:03,031
<i>Put him in the ring,</i>
<i>something new to punch...</i>

904
01:04:03,320 --> 01:04:05,151
<i>let me have a swing...</i>

905
01:04:05,320 --> 01:04:06,673
<i>then we'll go to lunch...</i>

906
01:04:07,480 --> 01:04:08,959
<i>then he'll get the drift.</i>

907
01:04:09,920 --> 01:04:11,797
<i>Put him in the ring,</i>
<i>chicken à la carte...</i>

908
01:04:12,160 --> 01:04:13,957
<i>let me have a wing,</i>
<i>tearing him apart.</i>

909
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:15,519
<i>The chicken will crow...</i>

910
01:04:16,120 --> 01:04:19,351
<i>let me have him, Joe.</i>

911
01:04:37,400 --> 01:04:38,037
He's got it.

912
01:04:39,280 --> 01:04:41,350
You sure this is going to work?

913
01:04:41,640 --> 01:04:44,200
Sure. Looks like a splurge gun.

914
01:04:44,560 --> 01:04:45,151
Doesn't it?

915
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:49,188
- Sort of.
- Nonsense.

916
01:04:49,480 --> 01:04:52,677
Anything Dandy Dan can
do, I can do better.

917
01:04:53,840 --> 01:04:54,750
Are you ready?

918
01:04:55,120 --> 01:04:55,711
Ready.

919
01:04:57,720 --> 01:04:58,755
Don't do that!

920
01:04:58,920 --> 01:04:59,796
Sorry, boss.

921
01:05:00,160 --> 01:05:01,070
All right, take aim.

922
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:04,591
Ready.

923
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:09,591
Get set.

924
01:05:12,040 --> 01:05:12,631
Fire.

925
01:05:17,520 --> 01:05:18,111
Missed!

926
01:05:18,760 --> 01:05:20,432
Back to the drawing board.

927
01:05:22,640 --> 01:05:23,356
Knuckles!

928
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:24,955
Knuckles, speak to me.

929
01:05:25,120 --> 01:05:25,711
Knuckles.

930
01:05:38,160 --> 01:05:40,628
It's all your fault, hear me?

931
01:06:00,960 --> 01:06:01,551
Hello?

932
01:06:03,440 --> 01:06:05,396
Not the grocery racket, too?

933
01:06:07,120 --> 01:06:07,711
Yeah.

934
01:06:09,000 --> 01:06:12,834
That's the whole empire
gone. Hear me? Everything.

935
01:06:13,200 --> 01:06:14,553
They'll be coming here next.

936
01:06:15,120 --> 01:06:16,155
There's only one thing for it.

937
01:06:16,720 --> 01:06:18,711
You have to get him to help me.

938
01:06:19,200 --> 01:06:20,315
Who? The Lone Ranger?

939
01:06:21,160 --> 01:06:24,869
No, Bugsy Malone. Call him.

940
01:06:27,760 --> 01:06:31,753
I'm in trouble, and all I got for
company is a female comedienne.

941
01:06:32,280 --> 01:06:34,350
I'm in trouble, bad trouble.

942
01:06:35,720 --> 01:06:36,311
Is he there?

943
01:06:37,440 --> 01:06:38,668
No. There's no answer.

944
01:06:39,680 --> 01:06:41,352
Then get him to me <i>poysanally.</i>

945
01:06:42,080 --> 01:06:42,671
Personally?

946
01:06:44,680 --> 01:06:46,796
<i>- Poysanally.</i>
<i>- Poysanally.</i>

947
01:06:52,120 --> 01:06:53,155
So long, lover boy.

948
01:07:18,280 --> 01:07:19,679
I like men at my feet.

949
01:07:20,160 --> 01:07:21,434
What you doing here?

950
01:07:22,000 --> 01:07:22,989
I brought you a message.

951
01:07:23,680 --> 01:07:25,159
What's wrong with Western Union?

952
01:07:25,600 --> 01:07:26,999
Thought you'd like the company.

953
01:07:28,720 --> 01:07:30,438
I'll buy you a drink.

954
01:07:30,680 --> 01:07:31,271
Where?

955
01:07:32,160 --> 01:07:33,195
How about Fat Sam's?

956
01:07:33,600 --> 01:07:35,511
Won't he be there?

957
01:07:35,840 --> 01:07:36,511
He sure will.

958
01:07:36,920 --> 01:07:38,672
Maybe I'll stay home.

959
01:07:39,520 --> 01:07:41,238
Don't flatter yourself...

960
01:07:41,400 --> 01:07:42,310
it's him that wants to see you.

961
01:07:42,960 --> 01:07:43,551
Come on.

962
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:45,991
Before your suspenders strangle you.

963
01:08:07,600 --> 01:08:09,670
Quit whistling, it makes me edgy.

964
01:08:09,920 --> 01:08:10,511
Yes, boss.

965
01:08:12,560 --> 01:08:14,516
- Pour me a double on the rocks.
- Sure, boss.

966
01:08:22,240 --> 01:08:24,276
What's funny? You find me amusing?

967
01:08:24,480 --> 01:08:27,040
I wasn't smiling at you.

968
01:08:27,200 --> 01:08:27,916
Honest, I wasn't.

969
01:08:28,080 --> 01:08:29,479
You find my suit funny?

970
01:08:29,640 --> 01:08:30,231
No, boss.

971
01:08:30,480 --> 01:08:31,196
It was your flower.

972
01:08:33,080 --> 01:08:35,230
Yeah, it is kinda droopy.

973
01:08:35,600 --> 01:08:36,476
Yeah, a little.

974
01:08:37,280 --> 01:08:38,679
In fact, it's very droopy.

975
01:08:39,320 --> 01:08:40,639
Very droopy, boss.

976
01:08:41,840 --> 01:08:42,750
Hold it a minute.

977
01:08:43,440 --> 01:08:44,429
It needs some water.

978
01:08:46,520 --> 01:08:48,272
Don't ever laugh at me again...

979
01:08:48,520 --> 01:08:49,953
or I'll ram that
smile down your throat.

980
01:08:50,320 --> 01:08:53,790
I'm Fat Sam, don't forget
that. Number one man, Mr. Big.

981
01:08:54,040 --> 01:08:56,156
Always have been,
always will be. Now get out.

982
01:09:01,960 --> 01:09:04,076
Careful, the floor is wet.

983
